The paper discusses the value alignment problem in robotics, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the design of collaborative robots, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a solution that combines decision theory and cognitive models of human behavior, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also emphasizes the importance of understanding human cognition, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the need for robots to adapt to their users' objectives, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
